{"atom_id":"ig34_p0236_a001","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":236,"page_region":"top","parent_section":"§6.3.5.5 Immunogenicity Specimen Assessments (IS)","atom_type":"SENTENCE","verbatim":"This example illustrates the use of the CDISC-recommended ISCAT values \"STUDY VACCINE-RELATED IMMUNOGENICITY\" and \"NON-STUDY-RELATED IMMUNOGENICITY\" to distinguish between immunogenicity and immunogenicity findings unrelated to the study vaccine data collected during a vaccine study.","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:writer","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2","ts":"2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0236_a002","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":236,"page_region":"top","parent_section":"§6.3.5.5 Immunogenicity Specimen Assessments (IS)","atom_type":"SENTENCE","verbatim":"ISCAT = \"NON-STUDY-RELATED IMMUNOGENICITY\" was developed to explicitly and purposefully indicate whether an observed immunity toward an antigen was not the study vaccine but rather was a result of natural infection or previous vaccination.","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:writer","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2","ts":"2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0236_a003","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":236,"page_region":"top","parent_section":"§6.3.5.5 Immunogenicity Specimen Assessments (IS)","atom_type":"SENTENCE","verbatim":"Oftentimes, it is simply impossible to tell whether the antibody found in a subject is due to a natural infection or previous vaccination (or both)—yet this immunogenicity, unrelated to the study vaccine, is important for collection and assessment at the screening phase of the trial.","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:writer","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2","ts":"2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0236_a004","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":236,"page_region":"top","parent_section":"§6.3.5.5 Immunogenicity Specimen Assessments (IS)","atom_type":"SENTENCE","verbatim":"In this example, immune responses against RSV-protein Z were measured during the study.","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:writer","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2","ts":"2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0236_a005","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":236,"page_region":"top","parent_section":"§6.3.5.5 Immunogenicity Specimen Assessments (IS)","atom_type":"SENTENCE","verbatim":"Because protein Z is not inserted into the vaccine vector, any immune response detected toward protein Z was not related to the study vaccine, although important for assessment and collected per the study protocol.","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:writer","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2","ts":"2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0236_a006","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":236,"page_region":"top","parent_section":"§6.3.5.5 Immunogenicity Specimen Assessments (IS)","atom_type":"SENTENCE","verbatim":"In order to show that RSV-protein B-induced antibody production was unrelated to the immunity solicited by the study vaccine RSV-protein B, the ISCAT = \"STUDY VACCINE-RELATED IMMUNOGENICITY\" (note: protein Z and protein B are examples, refer to controlled terminology for standard terms associated with ISBDAGNT).","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:writer","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2","ts":"2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0236_a007","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":236,"page_region":"middle","parent_section":"§6.3.5.5 Immunogenicity Specimen Assessments (IS)","atom_type":"LIST_ITEM","verbatim":"Rows 1-2: Show the screening and quantification of RSV-protein B antibody at baseline, prior to the administration of the study vaccine. Note: ISBDAGNT=\"HUMAN RESPIRATORY SYNCYTIAL VIRUS-PROTEIN B\" is the immunogenic target in the study vaccine (although it potentially eliminates the production of antibodies. Note: ISCAT=\"STUDY VACCINE-RELATED IMMUNOGENICITY\", even though at this point the study vaccine has not been administered to the subject, this is done purposefully to enable the grouping of baseline and treatment measurements.","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:writer","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2","ts":"2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0236_a008","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":236,"page_region":"middle","parent_section":"§6.3.5.5 Immunogenicity Specimen Assessments (IS)","atom_type":"LIST_ITEM","verbatim":"Rows 3-4: Show the screening and quantification of microbial-induced IgG antibody against the RSV-protein Z at baseline. Note: Because RSV-protein Z is not the immunogenic target of interest in this vaccine study, ISCAT is populated with the value \"NON-STUDY RELATED IMMUNOGENICITY\".","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:writer","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2","ts":"2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0236_a009","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":236,"page_region":"middle","parent_section":"§6.3.5.5 Immunogenicity Specimen Assessments (IS)","atom_type":"LIST_ITEM","verbatim":"Rows 5-7: Show the titer of microbial-induced IgG antibody against the RSV-protein B, post-vaccination at visits 1, 2, and 3. These 3 records show the antibody titers had increased post-vaccination, presumably due to the stimulation from the RSV study vaccine. ISCAT is populated with the value \"STUDY VACCINE-RELATED IMMUNOGENICITY\".","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:writer","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2","ts":"2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
