{"atom_id":"ig34_p0236_a017","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":236,"page_region":"middle","parent_section":"§6.3.5.5 Immunogenicity Specimen Assessments (IS)","atom_type":"TABLE_ROW","verbatim":"| 7 | RSV1230 | IS | RSV1230-011 | 3 | 13671 | | MBBGGAB | Microbial-induced IgG Antibody | HUMAN RESPIRATORY SYNCYTIAL VIRUS-PROTEIN B | QUANTITY | STUDY VACCINE-RELATED IMMUNOGENICITY | HUMORAL IMMUNITY | 1:500 | 500 | 500 | titer | SERUM | ELISA | | VISIT 3 | 2017-09-27 |","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:writer","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2","ts":"2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0236_a018","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":236,"page_region":"bottom","parent_section":"§6.3.5.5 Immunogenicity Specimen Assessments (IS)","atom_type":"SENTENCE","verbatim":"Thus far, all the IS tests illustrated are measurements of concentrations of a substance (e.g., antibody titer).","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:writer","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2","ts":"2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0236_a019","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":236,"page_region":"bottom","parent_section":"§6.3.5.5 Immunogenicity Specimen Assessments (IS)","atom_type":"SENTENCE","verbatim":"However, some immunogenicity tests are actual counts of immune cells that secrete a particular substance.","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:writer","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2","ts":"2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0236_a020","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":236,"page_region":"bottom","parent_section":"§6.3.5.5 Immunogenicity Specimen Assessments (IS)","atom_type":"SENTENCE","verbatim":"These tests are described by the combination of ISTEST (Immunogenicity Test or Examination Name) and ISMSCBCE (Molecule Secreted by Cells), where ISTEST identifies the type of cells that secrete a specific substance.","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:writer","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2","ts":"2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0236_a021","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":236,"page_region":"bottom","parent_section":"§6.3.5.5 Immunogenicity Specimen Assessments (IS)","atom_type":"SENTENCE","verbatim":"The following 2 examples introduce the IS domain-specific variable, ISMSCBCE, and illustrate its use with ISTEST to represent a complete immunological analyte of interest.","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:writer","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2","ts":"2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0237_a001","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":237,"page_region":"top","parent_section":"§6.3.5.5 Immunogenicity Specimen Assessments (IS)","atom_type":"HEADING","verbatim":"Example 6","heading_level":6,"sibling_index":1,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:writer","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2","ts":"2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0237_a002","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":237,"page_region":"top","parent_section":"§6.3.5.5 Immunogenicity Specimen Assessments (IS)","atom_type":"SENTENCE","verbatim":"This example shows data about the assessment of antibody-secreting cells (ASCs).","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:writer","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2","ts":"2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0237_a003","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":237,"page_region":"top","parent_section":"§6.3.5.5 Immunogenicity Specimen Assessments (IS)","atom_type":"SENTENCE","verbatim":"Traditional methods such as enzyme-linked immunosorbent assay (ELISA) that monitor humoral immune responses after immunization or infection typically only quantify specific antibody titers in serum.","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:writer","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2","ts":"2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0237_a004","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":237,"page_region":"top","parent_section":"§6.3.5.5 Immunogenicity Specimen Assessments (IS)","atom_type":"SENTENCE","verbatim":"These methods do not provide any information about the actual number and location of the immune cells that secrete antibodies or cytokines.","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:writer","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2","ts":"2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0237_a005","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":237,"page_region":"top","parent_section":"§6.3.5.5 Immunogenicity Specimen Assessments (IS)","atom_type":"SENTENCE","verbatim":"The enzyme-linked immunospot (ELISpot) assay is a method to detect and quantify analyte-secreting T or B cells.","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:writer","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2","ts":"2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0237_a006","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":237,"page_region":"top","parent_section":"§6.3.5.5 Immunogenicity Specimen Assessments (IS)","atom_type":"SENTENCE","verbatim":"During ELISpot testing, a colored precipitate forms and appears as spots at the sites of analyte secretion (e.g., cytokines or antibodies), with each individual spot representing an individual analyte-secreting cell.","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:writer","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2","ts":"2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0237_a007","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":237,"page_region":"top","parent_section":"§6.3.5.5 Immunogenicity Specimen Assessments (IS)","atom_type":"SENTENCE","verbatim":"The spots can be counted with an automated ELISpot reader system or manually, using a stereomicroscope.","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:writer","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2","ts":"2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0237_a008","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":237,"page_region":"top","parent_section":"§6.3.5.5 Immunogenicity Specimen Assessments (IS)","atom_type":"SENTENCE","verbatim":"This example shows how to represent the quantification of ASCs as the number of spots per million peripheral blood mononuclear cells (PBMC) as determined by B-cell ELISpot from a vaccine trial.","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:writer","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2","ts":"2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0237_a009","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":237,"page_region":"top","parent_section":"§6.3.5.5 Immunogenicity Specimen Assessments (IS)","atom_type":"SENTENCE","verbatim":"The IS domain-specific variable ISMSCBCE introduced in this example allows flexibility in data representation and post-coordination of the various secreted antibody types and their respective ASCs.","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:writer","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2","ts":"2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0237_a010","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":237,"page_region":"top","parent_section":"§6.3.5.5 Immunogenicity Specimen Assessments (IS)","atom_type":"SENTENCE","verbatim":"This approach liberates the ISTEST variable from having to house precoordinated and thus hyperspecific values crafted based on secretion and cell types.","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:writer","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2","ts":"2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0237_a011","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":237,"page_region":"middle","parent_section":"§6.3.5.5 Immunogenicity Specimen Assessments (IS)","atom_type":"LIST_ITEM","verbatim":"Row 1: Shows the total number of IgG ASCs from a subject's blood sample. In this case, ISTEST=\"Antibody-secreting Cells\"; the entity secreted by the cells in ISTEST is represented by the variable ISMSCBCE (i.e. IGG antibody non-specific to any antigen).","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:writer","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2","ts":"2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0237_a012","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":237,"page_region":"middle","parent_section":"§6.3.5.5 Immunogenicity Specimen Assessments (IS)","atom_type":"LIST_ITEM","verbatim":"Row 2: Shows the number of H1-specific IgG ASCs from the same subject's blood sample. In this case, ISTEST=\"Antibody-secreting Cells\"; the entity secreted by the cells in ISTEST is in ISMSCBCE (i.e. IgG antibody specific to H1 antigen).","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:writer","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2","ts":"2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
