{"atom_id":"ig34_p0237_a018","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":237,"page_region":"bottom","parent_section":"§6.3.5.5 Immunogenicity Specimen Assessments (IS)","atom_type":"HEADING","verbatim":"Example 7","heading_level":6,"sibling_index":2,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:writer","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2","ts":"2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0237_a019","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":237,"page_region":"bottom","parent_section":"§6.3.5.5 Immunogenicity Specimen Assessments (IS)","atom_type":"SENTENCE","verbatim":"This example shows data from the in vitro assessment and quantification of cytokine-secreting immune cells, expressed in number of spot-forming cells (SFC) per million peripheral blood mononuclear cells (PBMC) as determined by T-cell ELISpot from a vaccine trial.","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:writer","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2","ts":"2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0237_a020","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":237,"page_region":"bottom","parent_section":"§6.3.5.5 Immunogenicity Specimen Assessments (IS)","atom_type":"SENTENCE","verbatim":"Through vaccination, it is expected that cytokine secretion in immune cells is boosted whenever immune cells encounter the same virus and/or the previously exposed viral antigens.","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:writer","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2","ts":"2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0237_a021","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":237,"page_region":"bottom","parent_section":"§6.3.5.5 Immunogenicity Specimen Assessments (IS)","atom_type":"SENTENCE","verbatim":"By increasing this cytokine secretion, immune cells aid in the host defense and protection against (re-)infections.","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:writer","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2","ts":"2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0237_a022","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":237,"page_region":"bottom","parent_section":"§6.3.5.5 Immunogenicity Specimen Assessments (IS)","atom_type":"SENTENCE","verbatim":"In vaccine trials, this can be measured by isolating immune cells (e.g., PBMCs) from subjects at multiple time points during the trial and restimulating them with the virus or its viral antigens in vitro.","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:writer","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2","ts":"2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0237_a023","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":237,"page_region":"bottom","parent_section":"§6.3.5.5 Immunogenicity Specimen Assessments (IS)","atom_type":"SENTENCE","verbatim":"In this example, PBMCs were isolated from a subject participating a vaccine study for RSV and restimulated in vitro with either a RSV-antigen or without a stimulating agent.","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:writer","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2","ts":"2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0237_a024","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":237,"page_region":"bottom","parent_section":"§6.3.5.5 Immunogenicity Specimen Assessments (IS)","atom_type":"SENTENCE","verbatim":"At baseline (i.e., before vaccination), the RSV antigen-stimulated PBMCs produced minimal number of interferon gamma, as expressed in interferon gamma-secreting cells quantified in the number of SFC/10^6 PBMC (row 2), as compared to no stimulation (row 1).","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:writer","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2","ts":"2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0237_a025","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":237,"page_region":"bottom","parent_section":"§6.3.5.5 Immunogenicity Specimen Assessments (IS)","atom_type":"SENTENCE","verbatim":"Three weeks after vaccination, RSV-antigen stimulated PBMCs (row 4) showed significant increase in the number of interferon-gamma secreting cells compared to no stimulation (row 3) or baseline values (rows 1 and 2).","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:writer","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2","ts":"2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0237_a026","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":237,"page_region":"bottom","parent_section":"§6.3.5.5 Immunogenicity Specimen Assessments (IS)","atom_type":"SENTENCE","verbatim":"This suggests immunological memory of the immune cells after encountering the same microorganism or its antigens, and the switch of cell state from resting to active.","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:writer","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2","ts":"2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0238_a001","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":238,"page_region":"top","parent_section":"§6.3.5.5 Immunogenicity Specimen Assessments (IS)","atom_type":"LIST_ITEM","verbatim":"Rows 1-2: Show the measurement of interferon gamma (ISMSCBCE) cytokine-secreting cells (ISTEST) at baseline either with no stimulation (row 1) or stimulated with the RSV-antigen (row 2) in ISCNDAGT, respectively, prior to vaccination.","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:writer","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2","ts":"2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0238_a002","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":238,"page_region":"top","parent_section":"§6.3.5.5 Immunogenicity Specimen Assessments (IS)","atom_type":"LIST_ITEM","verbatim":"Rows 3-4: Show the measurement of interferon gamma (ISMSCBCE) cytokine-secreting cells (ISTEST) 3 weeks after vaccination and restimulation in vitro with the RSV-antigen (row 4) in ISCNDAGT and no stimulation (row 3), respectively.","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:writer","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2","ts":"2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
