{"atom_id":"ig34_p0240_a001","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":240,"page_region":"top","parent_section":"§6.3.5.5 Immunogenicity Specimen Assessments (IS)","atom_type":"HEADING","verbatim":"Example 10","heading_level":6,"sibling_index":5,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:writer","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2","ts":"2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0240_a002","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":240,"page_region":"top","parent_section":"§6.3.5.5 Immunogenicity Specimen Assessments (IS)","atom_type":"SENTENCE","verbatim":"This example shows how to present data from an autoimmune disease study, specifically how to represent information from disease-specific autoantibody tests.","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:writer","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2","ts":"2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0240_a003","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":240,"page_region":"top","parent_section":"§6.3.5.5 Immunogenicity Specimen Assessments (IS)","atom_type":"SENTENCE","verbatim":"Sjögren's syndrome (SS) is a systemic autoimmune disease characterized by dry eyes and dry mouth.","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:writer","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2","ts":"2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0240_a004","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":240,"page_region":"top","parent_section":"§6.3.5.5 Immunogenicity Specimen Assessments (IS)","atom_type":"SENTENCE","verbatim":"Diagnosis of SS is generally based on the detection of antinuclear antibodies (ANAs), that is, anti-Ro (SS-A) and anti-La (SS-B) antibodies.","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:writer","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2","ts":"2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0240_a005","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":240,"page_region":"middle","parent_section":"§6.3.5.5 Immunogenicity Specimen Assessments (IS)","atom_type":"LIST_ITEM","verbatim":"Rows 1-5: Show the screening (row 1) and quantification (rows 2, 4) of ANAs. Rows 2 and 3 are grouped together using ISGRPID=\"1a\"; this means the titer result in row 2 is specifically related to the particular finding in row 3. The specked pattern of the ANA is typically indicative of SS. Rows 4 and 5 are grouped together using ISGRPID=\"1b\"; this means the titer result in row 4 is specifically related to the nuclear staining pattern (i.e., nucleolar) finding in row 5. Rows 1 to 5 are grouped together using ISGRPID=\"1\", indicating that these records are related. The antinuclear antibodies test is post-coordinated and represented by both ISTEST=\"Autoantibody\" and ISBDAGNT=\"NUCLEAR AUTOANTIGENS\".","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:writer","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2","ts":"2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0240_a006","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":240,"page_region":"middle","parent_section":"§6.3.5.5 Immunogenicity Specimen Assessments (IS)","atom_type":"LIST_ITEM","verbatim":"Rows 6-11: Show the screening and quantification of the various SS-specific autoantiodies. SS autoantigens are represented by the ISBDAGNT variable, whereas the ISTEST=\"Autoantibody\".","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:writer","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2","ts":"2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
